  "time_ut": 1656583008,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Bus fare hike again is illegal - Private Bus Owners Association",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Kemunu Wijeratne, President of Sri Lanka Private Bus Owners Association, said that while 90 percent of private bus services are not in service, the bus fares have been increased again while public passengers are suffering.",
        "Increasing the bus fare is not an acceptable practice when the number of private buses plying in the transport service is limited due to acute shortage of fuel.",
        "Bus fares were initially revised to specify that passengers should travel only on the basis of the number of seats in buses during the Covid-19 outbreak.",
        "However at present it is not possible to load passengers on buses on seat basis only.",
        "No formal action has been taken so far to obtain the required fuel for the private bus service. Most owners get fuel from the fuel line.",
        "Indicates that bus fares have been revised to protect the private bus service industry. He said the public would boycott the private bus service in the near future as the minimum fare has been fixed at 40 rupees."
      ],
      "title_ents": [],
      "body_line_ents_list": [
